critique: This document is an executive order that delays certain transfers, consolidations, and eliminations provided for under section 4 of Executive Order No. 6166 of June 10, 1933, beyond the effective date of said order. It appears to be related to economic policy during the Great Depression. It is difficult to assess the ideological tilt without knowing the specifics of the transfers, consolidations, and eliminations. However, given the context of the Great Depression, it is likely that the order involves some level of government intervention in the economy. The order does not appear to have any direct impact on immigration, executive power, federalism, national security vs. civil liberties, or social inclusion. Therefore, the scores for these axes should be neutral.
